item.description:
You can submit scripts to run in Roar collab. Each script is called a job and you submit a job by providing a batch script to the SLURM scheduler. This script contains the resource specifications that your program needs to run.
Step 1: Create a job submit script. Below is an example of such file, called job_submit.sh.
#!/bin/bash #SBATCH --nodes=1 #SBATCH --cpus-per-task=4 #SBATCH --time=1:00:00 #SBATCH --mem=1GB #SBATCH --job-name=job_test #SBATCH --output=output_%j.log #SBATCH --mail-user=&lt;psu-id&gt;@psu.
